                            <comment id="122035" author="bzzz" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2015 17:50:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;LFSCK uses this protocol to access data on OST, so this will be affected too.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="122033" author="green" created="Thu, 23 Jul 2015 17:43:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;So is the perf regression only for DNE, DNE2? Or would single MDT configs be affected as well?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="121300" author="di.wang" created="Tue, 14 Jul 2015 22:49:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This seems important, so I will work on a patch before 2.8 release.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="119128" author="bzzz" created="Fri, 19 Jun 2015 17:37:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;well, the older versions don&apos;t support bulks, right? so, i&apos;d think it&apos;s a protocol change. then... I&apos;d say this is a performance regression because in the current release we don&apos;t need 2*RTT to fetch attributes (e.g., used all the time by LFSCK), it&apos;s a single RTT currently..&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="119125" author="adilger" created="Fri, 19 Jun 2015 17:30:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Alex, what is the impact of this issue?  It seems like only a potential performance improvement, but if this is a protocol change for the Async Commit code then I guess it needs to be in 2.8.0?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
